    <title>Integral formulation for migration in two and three dimensions</title>
    <url>/2023/08/13/Paper%20reading%20(1)%20Integral%20formulation%20for%20migration%20in%20two%20and%20three%20dimensions/</url>
    <content><![CDATA[<h1 id="Integral-formulation-for-migration-in-2D-and-3D"><a href="#Integral-formulation-for-migration-in-2D-and-3D" class="headerlink" title="Integral formulation for migration in 2D and 3D"></a>Integral formulation for migration in 2D and 3D</h1><p>​        Summation (integration) along a  diffraction hyperbola(衍射双曲线) was recognized as a way to  automate the familiar point-to-point coordinate transformation performed by interpreters in ==mapping  reflections from the x, t (traveltime) domain into the  x, z (depth domain).==<br>​        Migration can also be viewed as a downward continuation operation which transforms surface recorded data to a deeper hypothetical recording  surface.</p>
<h2 id="Theory"><a href="#Theory" class="headerlink" title="Theory"></a>Theory</h2><p>In homogeneous scalar wave equation</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
\nabla^2U-\frac{1}{C^2}U_{tt}=-4\pi q(r,t) \tag{1}</script><p>The complete solution to the equation is turned to be homogeneous wave equation and inhomogeneous boundary conditions of the Dirichlet type.  The remaining surface integral is given by</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
U(r,t)=\frac{1}{4\pi}\int dt_0\int dS_0 \left[G\frac{\partial}{\partial n}U(r_0,t_0)-U(r_0,t_0)\frac{\partial}{\partial n}G\right] \tag{2}</script><p>The specific geometry of interest is shown in Figure 1</p>
<p><img src="D:/JosieChourx/myblog/source/_posts/Paper%20reading%20(1)%20Integral%20formulation%20for%20migration%20in%20two%20and%20three%20dimensions.assets/1.jpg" alt="1" style="zoom:70%;" /></p>
<p><em><em>n</em></em><strong>n</strong> the outward normal vector to the surface $S_0$. 因此边值表示简化为一个包含 $S_0$ 上波场的表面积分和一个合适的格林函数 $G$. 由于方程 (2) 中的 $U(r_0,t_0)$ 等同于观测到的地质数据，因此使得在 $S_0$ 面上 $G=0$.  A Green’s function having  the desired properties at the free surface consists of  a point source at $r_0$ and its negative image at $r_0^{‘}$ .</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
G(r,t|r_0,t_0)=\frac{\delta(t-t_0-\frac{R}{C})}{R}-\frac{\delta(t-t_0-\frac{R^{'}}{C})}{R} \tag{3}</script><p>where</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
R=\sqrt{(z-z_0)^2+(x-x_0)^2+(y-y_0)^2}</script><p>and </p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
R^{'}=\sqrt{(z+z_0)^2+(x-x_0)^2+(y-y_0)^2}</script><p>将(3)式替换进(2)式，可以得到在任何点的波长 $U(r,t)$ 的积分表示。</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
U(r,t)=\frac{1}{2\pi}\int dt_0 \int dA_0 \cdot U(r_0,t_0)\frac{\partial}{\partial z_0}\left[\frac{\delta(t-t_0-\frac{R}{C})}{R}\right] \tag{4}</script><p><em><em>Kirchhoff integral</em></em><em><em>Kirchhoff integral</em></em>f integral**. </p>
<p>通过处理对 $z_0$ 的微分和对 $t_0$ 的积分，可以得到一个 (4) 的等价的表达式</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
U(r,t)=\frac{1}{2\pi} \int dA_0 \frac{\cos\theta}{RC}\left[U^{'}(r_0,t_0)+\frac{C}{R}U(r_0,t_0)\right]_{t_0=t-(\frac{R}{C})} \tag{5}</script><p>方程(4)的另外一种表示是通过将 $z_0$ 导数与 $z$ 导数交换，然后可以在积分外取</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
U(r,t)=-\frac{1}{\pi} \frac{\partial}{\partial z} \int dA_0 \frac{U(r_0,t-\frac{R}{C})}{R} \tag{6}</script><p>如前所述，积分变换方程 (4) 可以用其他符号来表示成三维卷积</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
U(x,y,z,t)=U(x,y,z_0,t)\ast\frac{1}{2\pi} \frac{\partial}{\partial z_0}\left[\frac{\delta(t\pm \frac{r}{C})}{r}\right]  \tag{7}</script><p>where</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
r^2=\Delta z^2+x^2+y^2</script><p>若对x, y和t进行傅里叶变换，则该表达式在频域上变为复乘法</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
\tilde{U}(k_x,k_y,z,\omega)=\tilde{U}(k_x,k_y,z_0,\omega)H(k_x,k_y,\Delta z,\omega)  \tag{8}</script><p>where</p>
<script type="math/tex; mode=display">
H = e^{\pm i|\Delta z|}\sqrt{(\frac{\omega}{C})^2-k_x^2-k_y^2} \tag{9}</script><p>传递函数 $H$ 是一个纯相位算子，体现了标量波动方程的色散关系。方程(7)和(8)中符号的选择很重要，因为它决定了推导的方向。如下图所示</p>
<p><img src="D:/JosieChourx/myblog/source/_posts/Paper%20reading%20(1)%20Integral%20formulation%20for%20migration%20in%20two%20and%20three%20dimensions.assets/2.jpg" alt="2" style="zoom:70%;" /></p>
<p><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em><em><em>positive sign</em></em>e sign** in operator H to extrapolate ==converging waves back toward their origins==.</p>
<p>为了更好的阐述方程(4)，即基尔霍夫积分方程，以及迁移原则，如下图所示</p>
<p><img src="D:/JosieChourx/myblog/source/_posts/Paper%20reading%20(1)%20Integral%20formulation%20for%20migration%20in%20two%20and%20three%20dimensions.assets/3.jpg" alt="3" style="zoom:70%;" /></p>
<p>输入假设是在 $Z=0$ 上堆叠的数据， 输出是在某些 $x,y$ 位置上的单轨迹。当receiver向下移动通过一些重叠的位置时候，通过计算 $t=0$ 的积分，在每一步都映射出一个点。</p>
]]></content>
